articles.author: Leonora LaPeter Anton, Brad Brooks
articles.description: An expanding Hurricane Milton made landfall on Florida's west coast on Wednesday, spawning tornados and lashing the region with rain as it threatened the Tampa Bay area, where it could deliver a life-threatening surge of seawater.
articles.title: Extremely dangerous Hurricane Milton makes landfall on Florida's west coast

articles.author: James Mackenzie, Maya Gebeily
articles.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said Israeli airstrikes had killed two successors to Hezbollah's slain leader.
articles.title: Hezbollah targets Israeli troops on Lebanese border, sirens in Beirut

articles.author: Sarah Marsh, Maria Tsvetkova
articles.description: Two pro-Russian activists said that German authorities have barred them from re-entering the country where they had been operating when a Reuters investigation last year revealed their ties to the Kremlin.
articles.title: Pro-Kremlin activists say they're barred from entering Germany

articles.author: Michelle Nichols
articles.description: Israel needs to address urgently "catastrophic conditions" among Palestinian civilians in the besieged Gaza Strip and stop "intensifying suffering" by limiting aid deliveries, its ally the United States told the U.N. Security Council on Wednesday.
articles.title: US calls out Israel at UN for 'catastrophic conditions' in Gaza

articles.author: Michelle Nichols
articles.description: A call by the U.S. and France for a 21-day truce between Israel and Hezbollah "is still on the table," said the top U.N. official in Lebanon on Wednesday as she pushed for a way to enforce a U.N. Security Council resolution violated for years by both sides.
articles.title: Top UN envoy in Lebanon calls for truce, UN resolution enforcement

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Argentina's lower house of Congress failed on Wednesday to muster the votes needed to reverse President Javier Milei's veto of a law that would have boosted university funding, a win for the libertarian leader after mass protests opposing his move.
articles.title: Argentina lawmakers fail to overturn Milei veto of university funding

articles.author: Hyonhee Shin
articles.description: South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol and Japanese Prime Minister Shigeru Ishiba were scheduled to hold their first summit on Thursday in Laos, Yoon's office said, as the neighbours seek to deepen security and economic ties.
articles.title: South Korea's Yoon, Japan's Ishiba to meet on sidelines of ASEAN gathering

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's National Bureau of Statistics said it will conduct a nationwide sample survey from Thursday to "accurately" monitor population changes and better plan economic and social policies, as authorities struggle to boost a fall in births.
articles.title: China to hold nationwide survey on population changes

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: More than 370 million girls and women alive today, or one in every eight worldwide, experienced rape or sexual assault before the age of 18, the United Nations children's agency said on Wednesday.
articles.title: One in eight girls and women raped or sexually assaulted before age 18, UNICEF says

articles.author: Yimou Lee, Ben Blanchard
articles.description: China has no right to represent Taiwan, but the island is willing to work with Beijing to combat global challenges such as climate change, Taiwan President Lai Ching-te said on Thursday, striking both a firm and a conciliatory tone.
articles.title: China cannot represent Taiwan and should work with Taipei on global challenges, Lai says
